<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Health and Safety Executive – written evidence</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Health and Safety Executive – written evidence</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The policy objective behind this proposal is to deliver Professor Lofstedt's recommendation by exempting those self-employed who pose no potential risk of harm to others.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">If the proposal is accepted, Section 3(2) of Health and Safety at Work etc Act 1974 (1974 Act)</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">will</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">read:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">(2) It shall be the duty of every self-employed person who conducts a relevant undertaking to conduct the undertaking in such a way as to ensure, so far as is reasonably practicable, that he and other persons (not being his employees) who may be affected thereby are not thereby exposed to risks to their health and safety.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">(2A) For the purposes of subsection (2), an undertaking is a relevant undertaking if -</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">(a) it is of a prescribed description, or</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">(b) persons who may be affected by the way it is conducted, other than the person conducting it (or his employees), could thereby be exposed to risks to their health and safety.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">consultation received responses from the following self-employed persons who classed themselves as businesses:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Farmer</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Lighting cameraman</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Nurseryman</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Tree Surgeon</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Director of an explosive company</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">All the above have the potential to cause harm to others so, even if they are not undertakings of a prescribed description, they would not be exempt from the law because of the provision in</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">s3(2A)(b) above. In other</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">words the duty can still apply if not on the prescribed list</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">. For clarity purposes the Government</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">is</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> seeking a delegated power for the Secretary of State to maintain existing safeguards and protections</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">for those self-employed who conduct their work in high hazard or high risk activities eg construction.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">This will be achieved through Regulations.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> The Government intend to consult further on the prescribed list but</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">agriculture and explosives are currently proposed</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">and consequently</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">self-employed persons working in those sectors would not be exempt .</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">For those occupations who don't fall into the prescribed list and</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">should</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">not be</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">exempt we will provide guidance. (eg the lighting cameraman's work could affect others by trailing cables creating trip hazards or unsecured lights falling on others).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">It is recognised that workers in some occupations pose a risk of harm to others only at certain times.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> On practical grounds</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">it was decided that only those self-employed persons whose work activities would not be expected to put others at risk at any point in the normal course of their work would be exempt, except, if they work in prescribed high hazard</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">or</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">high risk activities where all workers irrespective of their activity will not be exempt.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Sarah Wadham</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">HM Inspector of Health and Safety</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Operational Strategy, Enforcement and Accountability Unit</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Health and Safety Executive </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">5 November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>